pr_review_comment_body:
would you mind breaking this up a little bit so that the win7 and win8+ versions are separate functions?
That will help keep the diff smaller; logically you'd be renaming the existing method and adding the helper from this comment, and another method for the win7 logic.

```
const watchman_dir_ent* readDir() override {
   if (win7_) {
      return readDirWin7();
   }
   return readDirWin8();
}
```

Since both of the methods have the same signature, something like the following might work:
```
store.load_file_bytes(&fingerprint)
  .and_then(|res| {
    res.map(|v| Ok(v)).or_else(store.load_directory_proto_bytes(&fingerprint)))
  })
  .map_err(|e| (e, 1))?;
```
The challenge is definitely with the nested `Result`/`Option`.

@zilder You're right, of course. Maybe we'll add a default name generator later.

> Speaking of inlining, I can call create_replication_slot() from replicate() if slot_name != None

Sure, that would be nice.

how about we do these as enums in the object_table.h , like this:
```
enum {
  OBJECT_INDEX_SET = 0,
  OBJECT_INDEX_ADD,
  OBJECT_INDEX_PUBLISH,
  OBJECT_INDEX_MAX
};
```
This is what I'm doing in object_size PR. Gets rid of the #defines and gives you a consistent way of determining the size of your command set.
